@{b}@{u}WHAT IS RCS?@{ub}@{uu}


This is from the HWGRCS manual:

     @{i}The Revision Control System (RCS) manages multiple revisions
     of files.  RCS  automates the storing, retrieval, logging,
     identification, and merging of revisions.  RCS is useful for text
     that is revised frequently, for example programs, documentation,
     graphics, papers, and form letters.@{ui}  



RCS is ported to the amiga by Heinz Wrobel, under the name HWGRCS.
