@node "SHOW" "SHOW"
@toc "ARexx"
 @{b}SHOW@{ub}

Lets you choose which files will be displayed in the list.


Command         Parameters      Description
---------------------------------------------------------------------

SHOW            IN              show "checked in" files only
                OUT             show "checked out" files only
                BOTH            show all files
@endnode

@node "RESCAN" "RESCAN"
@toc "ARexx"
 @{b}RESCAN@{ub}

Scans the directory for new files.


Command         Parameters      Description
---------------------------------------------------------------------

RESCAN                          Updates file list
@endnode

@node "SELECT" "SELECT"
@toc "ARexx"
 @{b}SELECT@{ub}

Selects a new current file (the one that appears selected in the file list).


Command         Parameters      Description
---------------------------------------------------------------------

SELECT          NEXT/S          selects next file in the list
                PREV/S          selects previous file
                TOP/S           selects first file in the list
                END/S           selects last file in the list
                FILE/K/F        selects the specified file

Return 5 (WARN) if command failed, 0 (OK) otherwhise.
@endnode

@node "CHECKIN" "CHECKIN"
@toc "ARexx"
 @{b}CHECKIN@{ub}

Performs a Check In operation or simply opens the window.


Command         Parameters      Description
---------------------------------------------------------------------

CHECKIN         REVISION/K      specify revision number to be used
                STATE/K         specify state (eg. Exp)
                SYMBOL/K        specify symbol for this revision
                KEEPLOCK/S      will keep the lock on the file
                OPEN/S          opens the window (other parameters will be
                                copied in the gadgets)
                COMMENT/K/F     comment for this revision (always last!)

Example: CHECKIN STATE Rel SYMBOL foo COMMENT Ready to be released.
        Will check in the current file with state set to "Rel", the symbolic
        name of "foo" and the specified comment. No window will be opened.
@endnode

@node "CHECKOUT" "CHECKOUT"
@toc "ARexx"
 @{b}CHECKOUT@{ub}

Performs a Check Out operation or simply opens the window.


Command         Parameters      Description
---------------------------------------------------------------------

CHECKOUT        REVISION/K      specify revision number to be retrieved
                DATE/K          retrieves by specified date
                STATE/K         retrieves by specified state
                NOLOCK/S        do not gain lock on file
                OPEN/S          opens the window (other parameters will be
                                copied in the gadgets)

Example: CHECKOUT SYMBOL foo
        Will check out the latest revision matching the symbolic name "foo".
        No window will be opened.
@endnode

@node "LOCKFILE" "LOCKFILE"
@toc "ARexx"
 @{b}LOCKFILE@{ub}

Locks the file. Use this command if you have modified a file that was checked
in and you don't want to loose your changes.


Command         Parameters      Description
---------------------------------------------------------------------

LOCKFILE        FORCE/S         Don't ask for confirmation!
@endnode

@node "CANCELCO" "CANCELCO"
@toc "ARexx"
 @{b}CANCELCO@{ub}


Reverts to last checked in revision (or default rev.). To be used if you don't
want to keep your last changes to the file.

Command         Parameters      Description
---------------------------------------------------------------------

CANCELCO        FORCE/S         Don't ask for confirmation!
@endnode

@node "DEFREVISION" "DEFREVISION"
@toc "ARexx"
 @{b}DEFREVISION@{ub}

Change the default revision or branch to retrieve in a Check In operation if
no revision number/name is providied.


Command         Parameters      Description
---------------------------------------------------------------------

DEFREVISION     REVISION/A/K    default revision
@endnode

@node "EDITFILE" "EDITFILE"
@toc "ARexx"
 @{b}EDITFILE@{ub}

Edits the file with the configured editor.


Command         Parameters      Description
---------------------------------------------------------------------

EDITFILE                        Launch text editor with file as parameter.
@endnode

@node "SYMBOL" "SYMBOL"
@toc "ARexx"
 @{b}SYMBOL@{ub}

Adds or Removes symbolic revision names or opens the Symbol Manager window.


Command         Parameters      Description
---------------------------------------------------------------------

SYMBOL          ADD/S           Will add a symbolic revision name. You MUST
                                specify NAME and REVISION.
                REMOVE/S        Will remove a symbolic name. You MUST
                                specifiy NAME.
                NAME/K          name of the symbol to Add/Remove
                REVISION/K      revision number for the symbol to Add


Example: SYMBOL ADD NAME foo REVISION 2.13
@endnode

