QUIT                            Quits EasyRCS
@endnode

@node "QUERY" "QUERY"
@toc "ARexx"
 @{b}QUERY@{ub}

Asks information about the selected file or about global configuration. You
can obtain the name of the current file, its state (IN or OUT) and wich files
are shown in the list (OUT, IN, BOTH).


Command         Parameters      Description
---------------------------------------------------------------------

QUERY           FILENAME/S      Return the name of the selected file.
                CHECKSTATE/S    Checks if file is checked in or not.
                                RESULT= IN or OUT.
                SHOWSTATE/S     Returns the kind of files that are
                                shown in the list (OUT, IN, BOTH).


example:    OPTION RESULTS
            'QUERY FILENAME'
            name = RESULT
@endnode

@node "ASKSTRING" "ASKSTRING"
 @{b}ASKSTRING@{ub}

Opens a window to enter a text string, related to the given filename.


Command         Parameters      Description
---------------------------------------------------------------------

ASKFILE         TITLE/A         Title of the window.
                GADNAME/A       Name of the string gadget.
                FILENAME/K      Name of the file; if not provided "Global"
                                will be used.


Example: ASKSTRING "Enter New Symbol" Symbol FILENAME myfile.c
@endnode

@node "CONFIRMREQ" "CONFIRMREQ"
 @{b}CONFIRMREQ@{ub}

Open a two button requester to confirm an operation.


Command         Parameters      Description
---------------------------------------------------------------------

CONFIRMREQ      MESSAGE/A/F     Text to be displayed in requester.


Returns 0 for OK and 5 (WARN) for CANCEL.

Example: CONFIRMREQ MESSAGE "Really do that?"
@endnode

